The paper focuses on the resource allocation of the C-V2X multiple access mechanism for vehicular networks, which is a key aspect of network communication and falls under the category of network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the impact of different parameters on the performance of the system, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of simulation tools to analyze the performance, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the possible limitations and security issues, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
